fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.query.builder

Class AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder<B extends AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder<B>>

  • Object
    • AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder<B>
  • Type Parameters:
    B - the concrete implementation of this builder
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ATLQueryBuilder, GremlinQueryBuilder, OCLQueryBuilder

    public abstract class AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder<B extends AbstractMogwaiQueryBuilder<B>>
extends Object
    Provides a fluent API to create MogwaiQuery instances.

    This class defines the common methods that can be called on concrete builder implementations.

    Note: this class doesn't provide methods to associate a ModelDatastore to the created query. MogwaiQuery are used as an abstract layer that can be processed on any compatible(s) ModelDatastore(s) (see #process(AbstractQueryProcessor, List, Map).

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    MogwaiQuery, AbstractQueryProcessor

      • buildQuery

        protected abstract MogwaiQuery buildQuery()
        Constructs the MogwaiQuery instance associated to this builder.

        This method is called after validate() in build(), and as to be implemented by concrete subclasses to create the MogwaiQuery instance associated to the builder.

        Returns:
        the created MogwaiQuery
